<pdf_injection_guide>
<title>PDF GENERATION VULNERABILITIES</title>

<critical>PDF generation libraries often process untrusted input in ways that lead to SSRF, XSS, code execution, and data exfiltration. Testing must cover HTML-to-PDF converters like wkhtmltopdf and Puppeteer, LaTeX injection, PDF form manipulation, and embedded JavaScript execution.</critical>

<scope>
- SSRF via PDF generators
- XSS in PDF content
- LaTeX injection
- PDF form field injection
- Embedded JavaScript in PDFs
- Server-side resource access
- File inclusion attacks
</scope>

<methodology>
1. Identify PDF generation endpoints and input vectors.
2. Test for SSRF using internal URLs and file protocols.
3. Probe for XSS execution in PDF rendering context.
4. Test LaTeX injection if LaTeX-based generation is used.
5. Check for JavaScript execution in PDF viewers.
6. Analyze form field handling for injection.
</methodology>

